Awful Experience and Food  We went there expecting to have a nice evening because of the great reviews, but unfortunately we had bad service and disappointing food.  For starters, the server was obviously not happy to have customers. The added Covid precautions seemed to bother her especially when her thermometer broke.  Then, when we asked for a suggestion on the menu, she was annoyed and said that it was subjective.  I should have realized at this point that the food would also have a problem.  And it did!  How can you ruin pasta?  But they did. My tortellini was so salty it wasn’t edible, and when I asked her she told me it was the parmesan cheese.  I forced myself to eat it because I was so hungry, but I needed a gallon of water to wash it down. My husband’s pasta had the same “salty problem”.  To top it off, I noticed my plate was chipped. So don’t be fooled by the good reviews. This restaurant has problems and doesn’t want to return customers. They lost my business permanently!

This place was absolutely beautiful, and between the food and the atmosphere, I don’t know which was better. My friend and I originally came here because their desserts sounds scrumptious, but we ended up sharing the duck and the 2 hard ciders. The ciders were delicious and the duck, THE DUCK GIRL, was absolutely divine. The poached pear was out of this world and the reduction used to finish, I could’ve drank out a mug. Then to finish, we had the tiramisu and the panna cotta- and I have no words. The texture, the taste, and there wasn’t an overbearing sweetness, it was just simply perfect. We’ll definitely be coming here again to try their pasta 😋
